8:
Why... Did you help me... The Crown
of the Beast King is no more... There's
nothing for meâ€”
12:
Can't have my contractor dying on
me.
15:
Now then, what's next? What will you
use me for?
20:
There are no chains out there that
can tie us down!
32:
Well, whatever. I've lost interest. I
guess you're spouting nonsense too,
now.
35:
If you've lost your drive, just go
ahead and die. I can't help you with
this kind of thing.
41:
If the world didn't change, then
perhaps... I...
46:
We're to subdue the remaining
dogfolk rebels... An undesirable task.
50:
...They want to start a revolution by
making soldiers out of kidnapped
orphans? That's awful...
54:
Still, they don't pose much of a
threat. Why do you need our help
with this?
59:
Have you heard about the rumored
"Mysterious Mask" lately?
62:
Apparently the guy hides his face
and runs around saving kids, and he
doesn't take it easy on the
kidnappers.
67:
There's no telling whether this
person will agree to speak calmly
with us. So we need your help.
80:
Nimbus! There are children over
there!
86:
Teo! That man over there is still
breathing! Help him!
91:
Are you all right?! We need to patch
you up immediâ€”
94:
Ah... The mane... The man with the
mane...
111:
Long time no see, lion boy. Guess
you were still kicking after all?
120:
Well? The hell are you doing,
sneaking around like this?
132:
You wouldn't understand. You were
born into prestige, Whitetail.
134:
...The world did not change. I was
wrong, and I indeed added to the
world's sins!
137:
A sinner must seek atonement. Isn't
that right?
141:
I couldn't become like Teo, but I'll put
an end to this vicious cycle where
the oppressed become the
oppressors!
144:
None like me shall ever be born into
this world again!
156:
So you just cried and blamed
yourself? Nothing's changed.
164:
You jumped at the easiest answer
you could! Even Teo couldn't beat
any sense into you!
169:
Quiet! Don't you dare look down on
me!
172:
You were given EVERYTHING at birth!
You would never understand my
suffering!
175:
Enough! Get out of my sight,
Whitetail!
187:
I'm about done here. Can you
handle the rest, Teo?
196:
...Yeah. That's why I want you to put
him here. Don't worry... he doesn't
have the strength to go on a
rampage...
206: What is the meaning of this?
211:
...You were unconscious, and
Nimbus carried you back here. You
looked really tired...
216:
Get out of my way! What are you
doing this for?
219:
I must seek atonement, and yet that
Whitetail stood in my way, rambling
about senseless things!
224:
...Do you mean to say that you
understand who you are?
232: ...Then what am I supposed to do?
234:
My dreams amounted to nothing,
my place of death was wrong, and
even my attempt at atonement was
in vain...
236:
...Everything I do is wrought with
error.
239:
Somebody tell me... what my
purpose is...
248:
Perhaps you and that Little Lady
really aren't so different.
251:
You truly believe there is but one
path for you in life? 
...Though I can't see that Little Lady
ever-changing course.
254:
...Hey, kitten. I told you before, didn't
I? Sometimes running away isn't a
bad thing. So why did you return?
257:
There is more than one answer, and
there is more than one path. Give it
some thought.
261:
I'm going now, too.
...Good night, Magnos.
